JOHANNESBURG - The UDM is to respond to National Assembly Speaker Baleka Mbete and President Jacob Zuma in the Constitutional Court on Wednesday. It relates to the party's application seeking a secret vote in the motion of no confidence against the president. In her papers, Mbete indicates she isn't personally opposed to a secret vote, but argues that parliamentary and constitutional rules don't allow for anonymous ballots.Parliament was due to debate the motion on Tuesday.READ: EFF, IFP join UDM case for secret ballotBut the UDM, EFF and DA asked for a postponement after the Constitutional Court allowed the UDM direct access to argue its case.Now, the EFF and IFP have joined the UDM's application.Julius Malema's party believes there s a constitutional obligation to ensure a secret vote in this matter. eNCA